and the orgy of hindu-muslim bloodletting that followed partition led to the deaths of at least half a million and the migration of 12-14 million people. free india under nehru adopted a democratically-governed, centrally-planned economy. these policies were aimed at attaining "self-sufficiency", and to a large extent made india what it is today. india achieved self-sufficiency in food grains by the 1970s, ensuring that the large-scale famines that had been common are now history. however these policies also led to shortages, slow growth and large-scale corruption. after a balance-of-payments crisis in 1991, the country adopted free-market reforms which have continued 